      "recommendation": "Define explicit entry criteria and a complete permission matrix for all three tiers. At minimum, specify: (1) what verification steps move an account from unverified to partially-verified, (2) whether partially-verified accounts can withdraw, (3) whether partially-verified accounts can receive without limits."
    },
    {
      "type": "ambiguity",
      "description": "The 'daily transfer limit' does not specify whether 'daily' means a calendar-day window (resets at midnight in the user's timezone or UTC) or a rolling 24-hour window from the first transfer. This affects limit enforcement behavior at window boundaries.",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["End Users", "Product/Engineering", "Finance/Treasury"],
      "options": [
        "Calendar day resetting at midnight UTC — simpler to implement, predictable for users",
        "Calendar day resetting at midnight in the user's local timezone — better UX but more complex",
        "Rolling 24-hour window from first transfer — stricter control but harder to reason about"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Use calendar day resetting at midnight UTC for simplicity and auditability. Document this in user-facing terms as 'daily limits reset at midnight UTC.'"
    }
  ],

  "rejection_reasons": []
}

